1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:23,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,075 --> 00:00:40,545
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,545 --> 00:00:41,975
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:44,815 --> 00:00:46,755
(Episode 10)

5
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:11,045
Mr. Ha is a bit superstitious, isn't he?

6
00:01:11,875 --> 00:01:14,475
I've heard a lot of celebrities
are into that.

7
00:01:14,775 --> 00:01:17,715
Usually, it's the agency heads
who seek those things out.

8
00:01:18,385 --> 00:01:21,185
But at my company,
they were all raised Christian,

9
00:01:21,655 --> 00:01:22,755
so they can't stand it.

10
00:01:23,025 --> 00:01:24,925
Are you thinking of seeing someone?

11
00:01:25,025 --> 00:01:27,595
Just from time to time.

12
00:01:28,355 --> 00:01:30,395
I wish my mom had gone to see one.

13
00:01:30,695 --> 00:01:35,195
I sometimes think it would've been
better than therapy.

14
00:01:36,765 --> 00:01:39,405
I wish there were a pill that would
let me sleep for a few years.

15
00:01:44,245 --> 00:01:46,715
You don't have a care in the world,
do you?

16
00:01:49,745 --> 00:01:52,685
- You do?
- I've been through my fair share...

17
00:01:53,055 --> 00:01:54,115
when I was developing my game.

18
00:01:54,815 --> 00:01:56,955
There was no guarantee of success.

19
00:01:57,785 --> 00:02:00,625
I was getting older, and I only had a GED.

20
00:02:01,525 --> 00:02:03,465
Who was your celebrity crush?

21
00:02:04,765 --> 00:02:05,765
I didn't have one.

22
00:02:06,765 --> 00:02:08,295
What about now?

23
00:02:10,805 --> 00:02:12,105
I never said I did.

24
00:02:12,935 --> 00:02:16,475
You said you "didn't," past tense.
Doesn't that mean you have one now?

25
00:02:17,705 --> 00:02:18,775
You're right. I should be honest.

26
00:02:20,245 --> 00:02:21,245
Of course you should.

27
00:02:23,085 --> 00:02:24,085
It's you, Momo.

28
00:02:26,185 --> 00:02:27,215
Oh, my.

29
00:02:27,755 --> 00:02:28,755
Really?

30
00:02:29,485 --> 00:02:30,525
Yes.

31
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:31,855
From what role?

32
00:02:32,325 --> 00:02:34,255
I didn't fall for one of your characters.

33
00:02:35,925 --> 00:02:37,425
I guess you could say I fell for you.

34
00:02:39,365 --> 00:02:41,495
But you don't even really know me.

35
00:02:42,095 --> 00:02:43,535
If it weren't for Ju Shin,

36
00:02:43,535 --> 00:02:46,205
you wouldn't have even known I existed,
would you?

37
00:02:46,635 --> 00:02:47,675
That may be true.

38
00:02:53,345 --> 00:02:56,745
I heard games were everything
to you from Mr. Ha.

39
00:02:56,815 --> 00:02:58,045
That's not wrong.

40
00:02:59,685 --> 00:03:01,255
I bet my life on them.

41
00:03:01,855 --> 00:03:04,555
Are you going to keep
dedicating your life to work?

42
00:03:04,825 --> 00:03:06,695
It's not like I'm doing it all
by myself anymore,

43
00:03:07,725 --> 00:03:10,395
and I'm starting to think
I want to live like other people.

44
00:03:11,225 --> 00:03:13,695
But anyway, my brother has to
get married first.

45
00:03:14,635 --> 00:03:16,405
That's going to be tough for Mr. Ha.

46
00:03:16,805 --> 00:03:18,265
His standards are sky-high.

47
00:03:20,905 --> 00:03:22,135
I'm right here.

48
00:03:22,845 --> 00:03:24,275
Look no further.

49
00:03:25,375 --> 00:03:26,475
What is it?

50
00:03:28,575 --> 00:03:30,685
The chef wanted to know
how you enjoyed your meal.

51
00:03:30,915 --> 00:03:33,285
The portions were a bit large,
but it was excellent.

52
00:03:33,815 --> 00:03:35,755
- Same here.
- I'll pass that along.

53
00:03:40,555 --> 00:03:41,895
You have a bigger appetite
than I expected.

54
00:03:43,225 --> 00:03:44,665
I'm at the right age for it.

55
00:03:47,235 --> 00:03:51,705
My late mother used to love seeing
people heartily enjoy their food.

56
00:03:54,005 --> 00:03:55,945
That's such a sweet memory.

57
00:03:56,245 --> 00:03:57,475
I wonder if our dinner tonight...

58
00:03:59,075 --> 00:04:00,415
will become a fond memory too.

59
00:04:03,485 --> 00:04:04,915
Do you have surgery tomorrow?

60
00:04:05,415 --> 00:04:06,485
Pretty much every day.

61
00:04:07,885 --> 00:04:09,325
Whatever you do,
don't take up horseback riding.

62
00:04:10,455 --> 00:04:11,485
So many people get injured.

63
00:04:12,025 --> 00:04:13,595
Seungil Shipping's youngest daughter...

64
00:04:13,595 --> 00:04:16,395
She had a bad fall two years ago,
and I struggled to treat her concussion,

65
00:04:16,725 --> 00:04:17,795
but she went riding again...

66
00:04:18,995 --> 00:04:21,335
They say riding horses is
more addictive than meth.

67
00:04:21,335 --> 00:04:22,505
Is it really that bad?

68
00:04:23,835 --> 00:04:27,035
- Is that a real saying?
- Yes, it is.

69
00:04:27,605 --> 00:04:28,805
Can't say the same for
cows or sheep, though.

70
00:04:37,785 --> 00:04:39,385
You're surprisingly quirky and fun.

71
00:04:46,195 --> 00:04:47,625
Who's texting you this late?

72
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:48,695
It's for my taxi.

73
00:04:49,165 --> 00:04:51,325
- I will drive you.
- No, that's okay.

74
00:04:52,195 --> 00:04:53,235
I'm not sure how to feel about that.

75
00:04:55,705 --> 00:04:56,735
Are you wary of me?

76
00:04:57,505 --> 00:04:58,505
Yes.

77
00:04:59,935 --> 00:05:02,375
A woman has to be careful these days.

78
00:05:02,875 --> 00:05:04,445
Isn't it rude to be that honest?

79
00:05:09,245 --> 00:05:10,615
I don't want to impose.

80
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:13,455
How is it an imposition?
My driver's waiting.

81
00:05:29,505 --> 00:05:30,605
Please don't get out.

82
00:05:34,735 --> 00:05:35,745
Thank you.

83
00:05:36,575 --> 00:05:37,575
Alright.

84
00:05:50,225 --> 00:05:51,225
What is it?

85
00:06:00,595 --> 00:06:01,595
What's wrong?

86
00:06:03,035 --> 00:06:04,235
I feel dizzy.

87
00:06:04,935 --> 00:06:05,975
Dizzy how?

88
00:06:07,505 --> 00:06:08,505
Open your eyes.

89
00:06:09,275 --> 00:06:10,845
I can't.

90
00:06:11,145 --> 00:06:12,145
Open them.

91
00:06:13,075 --> 00:06:14,115
What's the passcode?

92
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,315
It's 1103.

93
00:06:51,715 --> 00:06:53,055
I've got you.

94
00:06:53,585 --> 00:06:54,855
It'll pass soon.

95
00:06:56,085 --> 00:07:00,095
Okay, first, I'm going to turn your head
to the left, 45 degrees.

96
00:07:07,695 --> 00:07:08,995
I'm going to count to 35.

97
00:07:09,505 --> 00:07:12,405
One, two, three,

98
00:07:13,235 --> 00:07:14,235
four...

99
00:07:21,175 --> 00:07:22,375
You'll feel better soon.

100
00:07:23,245 --> 00:07:26,155
One, two, three...

101
00:07:29,355 --> 00:07:30,825
Ever think about getting on
an operating table?

102
00:07:32,355 --> 00:07:35,755
Lie down just once,
and I can change your life.

103
00:07:39,265 --> 00:07:40,265
Go on in.

104
00:07:42,065 --> 00:07:44,365
I'm sorry. It was an important call.

105
00:07:44,365 --> 00:07:45,535
Of course.

106
00:08:14,265 --> 00:08:15,635
Have you ever been to this house?

107
00:08:16,405 --> 00:08:17,405
No.

108
00:08:18,035 --> 00:08:19,435
My father never invited you over?

109
00:08:19,875 --> 00:08:23,005
- No.
- Are you feeling better?

110
00:08:23,805 --> 00:08:24,805
Yes.

111
00:08:26,645 --> 00:08:28,915
I've barely been here
since my father passed.

112
00:08:29,515 --> 00:08:30,515
I just don't find myself stopping by.

113
00:08:31,215 --> 00:08:34,415
They say a house needs people living in it
to keep it from falling apart.

114
00:08:36,555 --> 00:08:37,585
That rock...

115
00:08:38,455 --> 00:08:39,955
is really cool and refreshing to sit on.

116
00:08:40,455 --> 00:08:42,865
When I got sleepy from studying,
I'd come out here to wake myself up.

117
00:08:45,295 --> 00:08:46,635
You don't like small dogs?

118
00:08:49,035 --> 00:08:51,765
Maybe it's because I was small and skinny.

119
00:08:51,905 --> 00:08:53,275
I'm drawn to big dogs.

120
00:08:54,705 --> 00:08:55,975
But he isn't a big dog.

121
00:08:56,505 --> 00:09:00,075
How am I supposed to raise a Retriever
in Yong Joong's apartment?

122
00:09:08,785 --> 00:09:10,425
You can raise ten Retrievers...

123
00:09:10,985 --> 00:09:11,985
in this house.

124
00:09:12,555 --> 00:09:15,595
Border Collies, Jindo dogs,
Chow Chows, Tibetan Mastiffs...

125
00:09:16,865 --> 00:09:19,835
You can have all the dogs you want,

126
00:09:20,835 --> 00:09:22,435
and we can live here, together.

127
00:09:24,705 --> 00:09:27,505
It's cliché, but I'm proposing...

128
00:09:31,245 --> 00:09:32,845
over two glasses of cold water.

129
00:09:36,015 --> 00:09:37,285
I'm not asking for much.

130
00:09:39,215 --> 00:09:41,515
Just have my children and raise them well.

131
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:44,955
I think we're on the same wavelength...

132
00:09:46,325 --> 00:09:47,795
when we talk or have any thoughts.

133
00:09:49,395 --> 00:09:51,195
I can have a decent conversation...

134
00:09:52,225 --> 00:09:54,265
- with just about anyone...
- I can't.

135
00:09:55,295 --> 00:09:56,365
I'm selective.

136
00:09:59,635 --> 00:10:01,435
Stop overthinking and complicating things.

137
00:10:01,435 --> 00:10:03,505
It's not about conditions...

138
00:10:04,475 --> 00:10:05,975
I'm not qualified,

139
00:10:07,075 --> 00:10:08,245
and we're not a match.

140
00:10:08,845 --> 00:10:09,845
What isn't?

141
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:23,195
Look, we're both on our own now.
No parents, no siblings.

142
00:10:24,465 --> 00:10:25,565
So what doesn't match?

143
00:10:25,965 --> 00:10:27,735
I've never even considered it.

144
00:10:28,335 --> 00:10:29,665
And it's completely out of the question.

145
00:10:29,665 --> 00:10:31,435
Nothing's out of the question.

146
00:10:32,365 --> 00:10:34,335
Everything people do is
more or less the same.

147
00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:35,875
Marriage.

148
00:10:36,345 --> 00:10:37,875
They call it one of
life's most important events,

149
00:10:38,605 --> 00:10:40,215
but it's just a man and a woman
living together.

150
00:10:40,215 --> 00:10:41,515
What's so special about that?

151
00:10:42,545 --> 00:10:43,845
Isn't it meaningful...

152
00:10:44,485 --> 00:10:47,215
to stay together with hearts unchanged
and not to get a divorce?

153
00:10:49,085 --> 00:10:50,285
I know what you mean.

154
00:10:50,925 --> 00:10:52,155
You're not wrong,

155
00:10:53,825 --> 00:10:55,155
but you never know until you try.

156
00:10:58,165 --> 00:10:59,465
So you're rejecting me
without a second thought?

157
00:11:00,195 --> 00:11:01,735
I'm taking that to mean
you find me completely undesirable.

158
00:11:02,335 --> 00:11:03,405
It's the opposite.

159
00:11:03,805 --> 00:11:05,335
You know best that,

160
00:11:05,605 --> 00:11:07,735
as for qualifications,
I'm the worst possible choice.

161
00:11:08,005 --> 00:11:09,675
I said let's not worry
about qualifications.

162
00:11:10,975 --> 00:11:12,875
I don't know my roots.

163
00:11:21,455 --> 00:11:22,725
The first humans...

164
00:11:23,755 --> 00:11:26,425
Think about the first life-form.
Did it have roots?

165
00:11:27,695 --> 00:11:29,825
The sky was their father
and the earth was their mother, right?

166
00:11:31,225 --> 00:11:32,595
Like the digital zero and one,

167
00:11:32,965 --> 00:11:35,765
life began from the combination
of yin and yang.

168
00:11:37,965 --> 00:11:39,575
Are these so-called qualifications
that people came up with...

169
00:11:40,635 --> 00:11:42,605
really that important?

170
00:11:45,545 --> 00:11:47,145
That's all they are. Just things.

171
00:11:47,845 --> 00:11:50,485
- You have a point, but...
- If I have a point, then don't argue.

172
00:11:54,255 --> 00:11:55,415
You don't see me as a man?

173
00:11:57,385 --> 00:11:58,485
To be honest...

174
00:11:58,985 --> 00:12:00,555
Then start now.

175
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:02,225
You could at least try.

176
00:12:06,435 --> 00:12:07,895
As a man, I'm flawless.

177
00:12:15,635 --> 00:12:17,045
A loveless marriage?

178
00:12:17,475 --> 00:12:18,775
Do you even know what love is?

179
00:12:19,815 --> 00:12:21,845
Define it. What is it?

180
00:12:27,585 --> 00:12:30,385
- Haven't you ever told Momo you love her?
- Leave Momo out of this.

181
00:12:31,055 --> 00:12:32,055
This is about us.

182
00:12:33,125 --> 00:12:34,595
I'm interested in you, Geum Ba Ra.

183
00:12:34,925 --> 00:12:36,025
Since when?

184
00:12:37,165 --> 00:12:39,665
This interest of yours could just fade.

185
00:12:39,795 --> 00:12:40,795
Even if it does,

186
00:12:42,905 --> 00:12:45,405
- let's do it.
- What are you really thinking?

187
00:12:46,065 --> 00:12:48,135
Is it like, "I'm not hungry,
but the table's set."

188
00:12:48,135 --> 00:12:50,645
"Even if it's not appealing,
let's just go through with it?"

189
00:12:50,805 --> 00:12:52,245
- Is that what this is?
- No.

190
00:12:52,915 --> 00:12:54,115
Stop questioning me.

191
00:12:58,545 --> 00:12:59,585
I hate complications.

192
00:13:00,955 --> 00:13:02,415
And I especially hate
having to explain myself.

193
00:13:03,785 --> 00:13:06,325
If you were my patient,
I'd patiently explain everything to you.

194
00:13:08,095 --> 00:13:09,765
I really can't.

195
00:13:09,765 --> 00:13:10,925
Because of your background?

196
00:13:12,465 --> 00:13:13,635
Or are you saying the problem is me?

197
00:13:13,635 --> 00:13:14,735
It's both.

198
00:13:15,895 --> 00:13:17,005
I'm sorry.

199
00:13:17,635 --> 00:13:19,005
But I do appreciate...

200
00:13:21,275 --> 00:13:22,535
you thinking so highly of me.

201
00:13:26,075 --> 00:13:27,215
I should get going.

202
00:13:32,185 --> 00:13:33,455
Is it because of Momo?

203
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:39,125
Is that what's holding you back?

204
00:13:40,455 --> 00:13:41,755
That's part of the reason, yes.

205
00:13:42,295 --> 00:13:44,695
We're like sisters.
It just wouldn't be right.

206
00:13:48,735 --> 00:13:49,865
What's that supposed to mean?

207
00:13:58,545 --> 00:14:00,775
Don't take a cab with the dog.
They'll give you a hard time.

208
00:14:01,715 --> 00:14:02,885
Nurse Park should be around.

209
00:14:53,565 --> 00:14:54,565
And so?

210
00:14:55,065 --> 00:14:57,605
Ankle monitors are for violent criminals,
right?

211
00:14:58,805 --> 00:15:01,075
I was so scared, and I was shaking.

212
00:15:01,575 --> 00:15:03,945
- Do you have his number?
- What are you planning to do?

213
00:15:05,245 --> 00:15:07,545
What if he holds a grudge against me?

214
00:15:07,915 --> 00:15:10,415
We'll have to figure something out
without confronting him.

215
00:15:10,485 --> 00:15:11,785
If he shows up again,

216
00:15:11,785 --> 00:15:14,155
tell security first,
then call me right away.

217
00:15:17,925 --> 00:15:18,925
Got it?

218
00:15:22,625 --> 00:15:24,695
I've become such a coward lately.

219
00:15:25,725 --> 00:15:27,065
I have no confidence in anything,

220
00:15:27,735 --> 00:15:29,635
and I keep having memory lapses.

221
00:15:30,535 --> 00:15:31,705
Lapses? How so?

222
00:15:32,165 --> 00:15:35,935
I can't remember bits and pieces
of my interactions with people.

223
00:15:37,845 --> 00:15:41,245
So if I ever forget something,
please try to understand.

224
00:15:42,145 --> 00:15:43,985
My doctor said that could happen.

225
00:15:45,345 --> 00:15:46,685
Your psychiatrist?

226
00:15:47,855 --> 00:15:50,255
I was just grasping at straws.

227
00:15:50,855 --> 00:15:53,425
I can't even trust myself anymore.

228
00:16:00,535 --> 00:16:03,105
I'm not very emotionally stable,

229
00:16:03,635 --> 00:16:06,035
and there's no way
I can get married in this state.

230
00:16:06,835 --> 00:16:07,835
So...

231
00:16:10,275 --> 00:16:11,375
Can't you understand?

232
00:16:12,275 --> 00:16:14,345
Putting myself in your shoes, I get it.

233
00:16:16,885 --> 00:16:17,885
Please eat.

234
00:16:18,385 --> 00:16:20,485
I barely notice my hunger these days.

235
00:16:20,655 --> 00:16:21,815
Would you like some wine?

236
00:16:22,715 --> 00:16:23,755
No, that's okay.

237
00:16:24,325 --> 00:16:27,095
The atmosphere here is so comfortable,
I don't need a drink.

238
00:16:28,055 --> 00:16:29,355
I guess I feel at ease...

239
00:16:29,925 --> 00:16:31,565
because I'm with you.

240
00:16:36,405 --> 00:16:37,405
Go ahead.

241
00:16:38,265 --> 00:16:41,005
To be honest,
hard liquor is more my style than wine.

242
00:16:41,775 --> 00:16:42,805
Whiskey, then.

243
00:16:43,405 --> 00:16:45,975
My treat. You're so busy,
but you still made time for me.

244
00:16:46,045 --> 00:16:48,515
No, I'm not really looking
to get drunk tonight.

245
00:16:50,515 --> 00:16:51,615
I'm just enjoying our conversation.

246
00:17:02,055 --> 00:17:04,025
Since you two are friends,

247
00:17:04,725 --> 00:17:08,465
I won't tell you how lonely and upset
Ju Shin made me feel.

248
00:17:08,635 --> 00:17:10,765
His upbringing probably
had something to do with it.

249
00:17:12,305 --> 00:17:14,535
To live up to
the late Director's expectations,

250
00:17:15,035 --> 00:17:16,905
Ju Shin worked really hard.

251
00:17:18,175 --> 00:17:19,775
I, at least, got to mess around
back in the day.

252
00:17:22,115 --> 00:17:23,485
Just try to remember the good times.

253
00:17:24,245 --> 00:17:25,245
Okay.

254
00:17:25,715 --> 00:17:28,115
The way you're explaining
everything so calmly...

255
00:17:28,415 --> 00:17:30,955
makes me feel a little less hurt.

256
00:17:33,555 --> 00:17:35,395
It must be hard for you to get away.

257
00:17:37,895 --> 00:17:38,925
I'll make time.

258
00:17:40,565 --> 00:17:43,435
You can be more casual with me,
like you are with Ba Ra.

259
00:17:45,265 --> 00:17:46,265
Got it.

260
00:17:47,305 --> 00:17:49,575
You're not this formal with her.

261
00:18:10,995 --> 00:18:13,365
He's way more down-to-earth
than Director Shin.

262
00:18:14,495 --> 00:18:16,395
And I am so ready.

263
00:18:35,515 --> 00:18:38,355
(Director Shin)

264
00:18:45,595 --> 00:18:47,695
What? Is your phone face down?

265
00:18:49,635 --> 00:18:51,935
- Yes.
- You made it home okay.

266
00:18:53,335 --> 00:18:54,335
Yes.

267
00:18:55,375 --> 00:18:56,405
Let me see you.

268
00:18:58,845 --> 00:18:59,975
This is awkward.

269
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:03,545
What's there to be awkward about?
I've already seen your place.

270
00:19:04,485 --> 00:19:05,585
Did you wash your face already?

271
00:19:06,885 --> 00:19:07,885
No.

272
00:19:09,085 --> 00:19:10,085
Then what?

273
00:19:12,055 --> 00:19:14,255
I'm not a big fan of video calls.

274
00:19:15,495 --> 00:19:17,065
It's awkward for me, too,

275
00:19:17,765 --> 00:19:18,895
but the moon is just so bright.

276
00:19:19,565 --> 00:19:20,565
It's a full moon.

277
00:19:22,595 --> 00:19:23,935
Go take a look outside.

278
00:19:24,765 --> 00:19:25,765
Okay.

279
00:19:26,265 --> 00:19:27,275
You're hanging up?

280
00:19:28,575 --> 00:19:29,575
Yes.

281
00:19:31,575 --> 00:19:32,575
But I don't want you to.

282
00:19:33,245 --> 00:19:34,415
I want to keep talking.

283
00:19:36,615 --> 00:19:38,345
The driver didn't give you
a hard time, did he?

284
00:19:39,415 --> 00:19:41,655
No, he was very nice.

285
00:19:43,555 --> 00:19:45,325
And here I thought
my proposal was considerate.

286
00:19:46,725 --> 00:19:48,055
Only to get shot down spectacularly.

287
00:19:50,495 --> 00:19:52,225
I'm not a big fan of
the whole marriage process either.

288
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:55,065
It's all for show anyway.

289
00:19:56,165 --> 00:19:58,005
Let's just see each other once in a while,

290
00:19:59,105 --> 00:20:00,375
grab a meal, talk,

291
00:20:01,835 --> 00:20:03,305
and raise a baby together like that.

292
00:20:07,215 --> 00:20:08,245
You don't like that idea either?

293
00:20:08,545 --> 00:20:10,015
That doesn't feel right.

294
00:20:11,385 --> 00:20:12,415
You say no to everything.

295
00:20:14,115 --> 00:20:15,585
Don't you want to be a mother?

296
00:20:18,555 --> 00:20:21,195
To be honest, I don't think
I'd be a very good husband either.

297
00:20:21,495 --> 00:20:23,765
Love is important to me, too.

298
00:20:25,825 --> 00:20:27,235
Are you just going to wait around
forever for love?

299
00:20:33,935 --> 00:20:36,975
I feel like we're a terrible match
and a great match at the same time.

300
00:20:38,405 --> 00:20:39,405
At least, I do.

301
00:20:39,805 --> 00:20:41,515
You were raised like a prince,

302
00:20:42,215 --> 00:20:44,145
and emotionally, you're a bit...

303
00:20:44,445 --> 00:20:45,445
A bit what?

304
00:20:45,885 --> 00:20:48,285
Cold? Or maybe detached?

305
00:20:49,055 --> 00:20:50,585
I'm sure it's your job, though.

306
00:20:51,955 --> 00:20:53,025
Someone's told me that before.

307
00:20:54,155 --> 00:20:55,695
That I can be pretty inconsiderate.

308
00:20:56,295 --> 00:20:57,395
And I admit it.

309
00:20:58,325 --> 00:20:59,965
You just swapped "inconsiderate"
for "emotionally detached."

310
00:21:01,095 --> 00:21:02,695
What can I do? That's just how I'm wired.

311
00:21:03,265 --> 00:21:05,835
As long as you're not bothering anyone,
it's fine.

312
00:21:06,365 --> 00:21:07,635
Do you really think so?

313
00:21:08,335 --> 00:21:10,845
- Yes.
- Then don't just think it.

314
00:21:11,105 --> 00:21:12,105
Warm up to me.

315
00:21:13,475 --> 00:21:14,845
I was looking at the moon,

316
00:21:14,845 --> 00:21:16,685
and I thought about how you rejected me.

317
00:21:18,045 --> 00:21:20,355
I wondered, "Why was I rejected?"
I just kept thinking...

318
00:21:21,315 --> 00:21:23,855
I got it wrong.
I really thought you'd say yes.

319
00:21:25,885 --> 00:21:27,395
You're not the type...

320
00:21:28,795 --> 00:21:30,065
to play hard to get.

321
00:21:31,495 --> 00:21:34,995
I'd cleared my schedule
for a week to marry Momo,

322
00:21:36,495 --> 00:21:37,905
so how about we take a
walking-and-reading tour?

323
00:21:40,805 --> 00:21:41,805
A trip?

324
00:21:42,075 --> 00:21:44,205
Yes. Provence is a great place to walk.

325
00:21:44,805 --> 00:21:46,445
The scenery is a work of art
everywhere you go.

326
00:21:49,215 --> 00:21:50,545
And you're on leave from work.

327
00:21:50,615 --> 00:21:51,785
I'll be the one to compromise again.

328
00:21:53,245 --> 00:21:54,585
We don't have to have kids.

329
00:21:54,715 --> 00:21:55,785
We can just be friends
who understand each other.

330
00:21:55,855 --> 00:21:58,455
I can't possibly see you as a friend,
Director Shin.

331
00:22:00,455 --> 00:22:01,825
You don't have to force it.

332
00:22:02,955 --> 00:22:05,095
- As just an acquaintance then.
- Not even as an acquaintance.

333
00:22:05,995 --> 00:22:06,995
Then what am I supposed to do?

334
00:22:09,195 --> 00:22:11,765
- You should talk to Momo again...
- Don't mention Momo.

335
00:22:12,165 --> 00:22:14,905
I've already put her out of my mind.
I've erased her.

336
00:22:16,075 --> 00:22:18,475
I don't have the luxury or the reason
to dwell on bad memories.

337
00:22:18,545 --> 00:22:20,075
Is it really that easy for you?

338
00:22:24,285 --> 00:22:27,315
But don't you have more loving memories
than bad ones?

339
00:22:28,255 --> 00:22:29,385
She lost my baby.

340
00:22:31,455 --> 00:22:33,525
- She didn't on purpose...
- Let's not talk about that.

341
00:22:35,255 --> 00:22:37,525
Go inside before the mosquitoes get you.

342
00:22:37,525 --> 00:22:38,625
Are you worried about me?

343
00:22:42,195 --> 00:22:43,195
Alright.

344
00:22:44,265 --> 00:22:45,805
Make sure you look at the moon.

345
00:22:46,665 --> 00:22:48,435
It's been years
since I've really looked at the moon.

346
00:22:50,905 --> 00:22:52,275
Anyway,
the universe is a mysterious place.

347
00:22:53,075 --> 00:22:54,075
Yes.

348
00:22:54,915 --> 00:22:56,575
Do your premonitions usually come true?

349
00:23:00,355 --> 00:23:01,815
The one I just had...

350
00:23:04,825 --> 00:23:06,285
showed me that in the end,
you'll be by my side.

351
00:23:07,325 --> 00:23:08,325
Geum Ba Ra.

352
00:23:12,995 --> 00:23:14,865
(Geum Ba Ra)

353
00:23:45,565 --> 00:23:48,395
Do you really think he came
just for his daughter's picture?

354
00:23:48,835 --> 00:23:50,935
If he's her father, it's understandable.

355
00:23:51,765 --> 00:23:52,765
Yong Joong.

356
00:23:54,005 --> 00:23:55,675
You're nine years older than me.

357
00:23:56,875 --> 00:23:57,975
Just for today.

358
00:23:59,345 --> 00:24:01,215
It's a hard habit to break.

359
00:24:03,245 --> 00:24:06,445
Anyway, if he comes back,
don't roll down your window.

360
00:24:12,025 --> 00:24:14,025
Have you ever met Kim Jin Ju?

361
00:25:00,205 --> 00:25:01,205
Who is it?

362
00:25:02,135 --> 00:25:03,135
I'm an employee.

363
00:25:03,705 --> 00:25:06,505
I'm here to drop off Mr. Ha's outfit
for tomorrow.

364
00:25:07,245 --> 00:25:09,445
Right. I'm heading into the room,

365
00:25:10,015 --> 00:25:11,015
so you can come out.

366
00:25:13,485 --> 00:25:14,485
Okay.

367
00:25:39,005 --> 00:25:40,975
You don't remember me, do you?

368
00:25:42,845 --> 00:25:46,515
You gave me a ride last summer
on a rainy day.

369
00:25:47,015 --> 00:25:48,855
You even gave me 100 dollars
for the taxi too.

370
00:25:51,625 --> 00:25:52,925
In front of my brother's company?

371
00:25:53,825 --> 00:25:55,855
- Yes.
- So you got the job?

372
00:25:56,555 --> 00:25:57,695
Yes, thanks to you.

373
00:25:57,965 --> 00:25:59,425
I didn't really do anything.

374
00:25:59,795 --> 00:26:02,795
- Good for you.
- I'll just leave the taxi fare here.

375
00:26:03,265 --> 00:26:04,965
I was so grateful that day.

376
00:26:05,605 --> 00:26:07,605
Treat me to a meal instead.

377
00:26:10,075 --> 00:26:12,075
I'll just leave the taxi fare here.

378
00:26:12,475 --> 00:26:14,215
I was so grateful that day.

379
00:26:15,145 --> 00:26:16,145
Don't worry about it.

380
00:26:24,425 --> 00:26:25,425
I'll be going now.

381
00:26:25,855 --> 00:26:26,855
Okay.

382
00:26:41,175 --> 00:26:43,005
He had a killer body.

383
00:26:43,505 --> 00:26:45,705
I knew her because
she worked for my brother.

384
00:26:47,075 --> 00:26:48,645
But she looked like
a completely different person...

385
00:26:49,315 --> 00:26:50,745
in that photo in the recent article.

386
00:26:52,485 --> 00:26:54,615
She's gotten a lot prettier
working with me.

387
00:26:56,315 --> 00:26:59,525
First, my mom passes away,
and now my stylist...

388
00:27:00,825 --> 00:27:02,925
When it rains, it pours.

389
00:27:04,095 --> 00:27:06,025
I really need to hold it together.

390
00:27:06,295 --> 00:27:09,365
But having Ba Ra around
must be a big help, right?

391
00:27:11,035 --> 00:27:12,735
She's lonely to the bone.

392
00:27:13,205 --> 00:27:16,335
So being around her can really
bring you down sometimes.

393
00:27:17,745 --> 00:27:18,745
Really?

394
00:27:19,205 --> 00:27:22,275
Yes.
Your upbringing really makes a difference.

395
00:27:25,445 --> 00:27:26,745
Can't you tell?

396
00:27:27,815 --> 00:27:28,815
Not really...

397
00:27:31,025 --> 00:27:32,125
Enjoy your meal.

398
00:27:32,385 --> 00:27:34,325
I guess she only lets her guard down
around me.

399
00:27:41,465 --> 00:27:43,295
She tends to try to be cheerful, though.

400
00:27:43,935 --> 00:27:45,805
Maybe it's because
she's comfortable with me.

401
00:27:47,475 --> 00:27:48,705
That doesn't sound like her.

402
00:27:50,175 --> 00:27:51,945
So what did you think of Kim Jin Ju?

403
00:27:52,705 --> 00:27:54,545
I'm not good at getting a read on women.

404
00:27:55,375 --> 00:27:56,845
Don't you guys look at a woman's face?

405
00:27:57,345 --> 00:27:59,315
I don't pay close attention
if I don't have a reason to.

406
00:27:59,915 --> 00:28:01,715
So he wasn't interested in the slightest?

407
00:28:03,455 --> 00:28:04,755
She once...

408
00:28:05,425 --> 00:28:06,725
mentioned you to me.

409
00:28:07,625 --> 00:28:10,225
- What'd she say?
- That you're considerate.

410
00:28:11,125 --> 00:28:12,825
She said you even gave her money
for her taxi.

411
00:28:12,925 --> 00:28:15,335
Women must be born with amazing memories.

412
00:28:15,495 --> 00:28:18,835
We don't forget things that leave a mark,
either good or bad.

413
00:28:19,265 --> 00:28:20,635
Should I ask Ba Ra to come out?

414
00:28:21,175 --> 00:28:23,435
- Are you uncomfortable?
- No.

415
00:28:24,075 --> 00:28:26,145
Three's more fun than two,
don't you think?

416
00:28:27,445 --> 00:28:29,115
Should we invite her for a second round?

417
00:28:33,815 --> 00:28:35,655
I might as well rub it in
right in front of her face.

418
00:28:36,085 --> 00:28:37,725
The phone is turned off...

419
00:28:38,155 --> 00:28:39,155
It's off.

420
00:28:39,825 --> 00:28:41,425
She's always has it turned off these days.

421
00:28:41,655 --> 00:28:44,325
She probably keeps getting work calls
from people who don't know she's on leave.

422
00:28:49,935 --> 00:28:51,565
Let's just crash her place.

423
00:28:54,775 --> 00:28:56,035
She might have gone to bed early.

424
00:29:01,445 --> 00:29:05,015
- Sorry, the shoot ran late.
- What shoot?

425
00:29:05,285 --> 00:29:06,745
What's next?
Are you making your acting debut now?

426
00:29:06,815 --> 00:29:10,415
A magazine shoot for Choi Hoon,
so I had to be there.

427
00:29:11,785 --> 00:29:12,955
Your brother is here.

428
00:29:13,385 --> 00:29:14,395
Ha Yong Joong?

429
00:29:14,725 --> 00:29:16,695
- Yes.
- Who's he with?

430
00:29:16,895 --> 00:29:17,895
With Momo.

431
00:29:18,495 --> 00:29:19,495
Momo?

432
00:29:20,395 --> 00:29:21,395
The Momo?

433
00:29:24,765 --> 00:29:26,765
Let's get drinks next time
for a proper cheer me up.

434
00:29:26,765 --> 00:29:27,835
Okay.

435
00:29:31,775 --> 00:29:32,875
Hey, James.

436
00:29:33,345 --> 00:29:34,745
Mr. Ha!

437
00:29:35,045 --> 00:29:36,245
I heard you two were here.

438
00:29:36,745 --> 00:29:39,245
- I'm with Park Ho.
- Oh, Park Ho.

439
00:29:40,245 --> 00:29:41,455
Mind if we join you?

440
00:29:41,755 --> 00:29:42,755
Of course.

441
00:29:44,955 --> 00:29:46,485
He's the son of the CEO
of Hanik Pharmaceuticals,

442
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:47,895
and he's a huge fan of yours.

443
00:29:49,055 --> 00:29:50,225
I see...

444
00:29:54,595 --> 00:29:56,095
How pathetic.

445
00:29:56,695 --> 00:29:59,005
- I should probably get going.
- Why?

446
00:30:00,035 --> 00:30:01,405
I'd just be in the way.

447
00:30:01,405 --> 00:30:03,075
What do you mean? He's a huge fan.

448
00:30:03,205 --> 00:30:04,445
He's like family to us.

449
00:30:04,505 --> 00:30:07,005
He's also really well-connected.
It's good to know him.

450
00:30:11,615 --> 00:30:12,885
Hey, it's been a while.

451
00:30:12,885 --> 00:30:14,885
Tell me about it. Not since
you've become a huge success.

452
00:30:14,955 --> 00:30:17,485
- Come on.
- You're a total icon these days.

453
00:30:17,555 --> 00:30:18,725
Those are baseless rumors.

454
00:30:19,485 --> 00:30:20,795
Even my twins...

455
00:30:23,455 --> 00:30:26,025
What? I look a little better, don't I?

456
00:30:26,725 --> 00:30:29,035
- You got the fat redistributed?
- Yes.

457
00:30:30,765 --> 00:30:31,765
Momo.

458
00:30:32,105 --> 00:30:33,705
Goodness, it's truly an honor.

459
00:30:34,375 --> 00:30:35,435
May I have a handshake?

460
00:30:38,375 --> 00:30:40,845
You're even prettier in person.

461
00:30:40,845 --> 00:30:42,115
Thank you.

462
00:30:49,085 --> 00:30:51,725
- Why aren't you heading home?
- Are you two dating already?

463
00:30:52,485 --> 00:30:53,755
What are you talking about?

464
00:30:54,025 --> 00:30:55,755
Stop dodging the question and sit down.

465
00:30:56,925 --> 00:30:58,325
I was just getting some water.

466
00:31:00,735 --> 00:31:01,995
I'll have ice water.

467
00:31:14,115 --> 00:31:15,145
(Discovery of the Mind)

468
00:31:19,745 --> 00:31:21,585
Let's just see each other once in a while,

469
00:31:22,455 --> 00:31:23,785
grab a meal, talk,

470
00:31:24,625 --> 00:31:26,285
and raise a baby together like that.

471
00:31:34,235 --> 00:31:35,965
What do you call it if not a date?
It was just the two of you.

472
00:31:36,265 --> 00:31:37,535
The same with Momo.

473
00:31:37,535 --> 00:31:39,965
She just called off her engagement.
And with you, of all people.

474
00:31:40,105 --> 00:31:41,905
She just sees me as an older brother.

475
00:31:41,905 --> 00:31:43,435
An older brother?

476
00:31:43,575 --> 00:31:45,945
But that's not you, right?

477
00:31:47,075 --> 00:31:49,175
We just had a meal.
Don't read too much into it.

478
00:31:49,245 --> 00:31:50,545
Not all meals are the same.

479
00:31:50,815 --> 00:31:52,785
With me, it would've just been a meal.

480
00:31:52,915 --> 00:31:54,755
Imagine how pathetic you'd look
if Ju Shin found out.

481
00:31:54,885 --> 00:31:58,225
- It's not like we're strangers.
- That's all the more reason.

482
00:31:58,685 --> 00:31:59,955
You need to keep your distance.

483
00:32:03,795 --> 00:32:05,625
At the end of the day,
you're just another guy.

484
00:32:06,065 --> 00:32:08,565
Smitten by a young, pretty face
and can't think straight.

485
00:32:08,965 --> 00:32:10,935
Do you really want to insult
your own brother like that?

486
00:32:11,005 --> 00:32:13,735
- Am I wrong?
- It's not what you say, but your tone.

487
00:32:14,005 --> 00:32:15,505
If you were me, would you ignore it?

488
00:32:15,635 --> 00:32:17,235
Her mom died so suddenly,

489
00:32:17,305 --> 00:32:19,875
- her stylist died, she called it off...
- She was the one...

490
00:32:19,945 --> 00:32:21,215
who ended the engagement.

491
00:32:21,275 --> 00:32:24,585
Her stylist's dad, on an ankle monitor,
suddenly blocked her car.

492
00:32:24,645 --> 00:32:25,685
How could she not be terrified?

493
00:32:26,845 --> 00:32:29,455
Look, whatever the reason,
just stay away from her.

494
00:32:29,685 --> 00:32:33,585
If a man and woman see each other often,
they're bound to catch feelings.

495
00:32:34,755 --> 00:32:37,965
I read your article.
Your writing is very concise and good.

496
00:32:38,595 --> 00:32:40,695
- You read it?
- Of course. Why wouldn't I?

497
00:32:41,835 --> 00:32:44,265
You turned our short chat
into an "exclusive interview."

498
00:32:46,535 --> 00:32:48,105
Ever thought about being an author?

499
00:32:49,105 --> 00:32:51,605
I think you have the talent for it.

500
00:32:51,745 --> 00:32:54,015
The Russian author,
Nikolay Karamzin, said that...

501
00:32:54,545 --> 00:32:56,715
writing portrays the soul and the heart,

502
00:32:56,975 --> 00:32:59,215
so a bad person
can never be a good writer.

503
00:32:59,915 --> 00:33:01,415
Does that mean you're a bad person?

504
00:33:03,215 --> 00:33:04,225
You're not.

505
00:33:04,655 --> 00:33:05,925
How would you know?

506
00:33:08,525 --> 00:33:11,765
- Here is our signature burger.
- Thank you.

507
00:33:12,165 --> 00:33:13,465
A burger's not complete without a Cola.

508
00:33:14,265 --> 00:33:15,335
I'll have one, then.

509
00:33:16,095 --> 00:33:17,095
With ice?

510
00:33:17,095 --> 00:33:19,265
- Yes.
- Me too, please.

511
00:33:22,905 --> 00:33:23,905
You're an F, right?

512
00:33:24,975 --> 00:33:26,445
And you're a T, aren't you?

513
00:33:26,645 --> 00:33:28,915
I don't know. I've never taken it.

514
00:33:29,575 --> 00:33:30,885
Do you want to take it now?

515
00:33:32,515 --> 00:33:33,685
It's beneath my dignity.

516
00:33:34,355 --> 00:33:36,855
To be defined by a test
someone else created.

517
00:33:37,625 --> 00:33:40,555
You're right.
My results change every time I take it.

518
00:33:43,455 --> 00:33:45,495
Do you really think you're a bad person?

519
00:33:49,265 --> 00:33:51,265
I don't feel like I'm a good person.

520
00:33:51,265 --> 00:33:52,965
As long as you don't feel
like a bad person, it's fine.

521
00:33:54,135 --> 00:33:55,235
It means you have a conscience.

522
00:33:56,675 --> 00:33:58,345
You're just being considerate.

523
00:33:58,975 --> 00:34:00,775
I have no reason to be considerate.

524
00:34:02,545 --> 00:34:05,485
Name one reason you think you're
a bad person.

525
00:34:07,285 --> 00:34:09,985
There are too many to name just one.

526
00:34:12,955 --> 00:34:14,025
Is it because of your job?

527
00:34:14,995 --> 00:34:16,555
Are all reporters that slick?

528
00:34:17,395 --> 00:34:18,895
Like a fox, to put it bluntly?

529
00:34:21,435 --> 00:34:23,065
You don't show your true colors,
is that it?

530
00:34:23,835 --> 00:34:25,535
It's always, "Director Shin."

531
00:34:26,765 --> 00:34:28,205
You're polite,
but it feels like you don't trust me.

532
00:34:29,975 --> 00:34:31,405
Are you an untrustworthy person?

533
00:34:32,145 --> 00:34:33,145
No.

534
00:34:33,675 --> 00:34:36,575
To be honest,
I'm trying not to cross any lines,

535
00:34:36,645 --> 00:34:39,285
so I'm always on my toes
and keeping my guard up.

536
00:34:39,615 --> 00:34:41,115
You don't seem tense at all.

537
00:34:42,155 --> 00:34:43,185
Are you playing poker?

538
00:34:44,455 --> 00:34:45,885
Are you saying I have a poker face?

539
00:34:46,825 --> 00:34:47,895
Now I'm curious...

540
00:34:48,655 --> 00:34:50,625
to see what happens
when you're not so focused...

541
00:34:51,065 --> 00:34:52,465
and finally cross that line.

542
00:34:53,595 --> 00:34:55,995
You might not want to see me ever again.

543
00:34:57,295 --> 00:34:58,535
Go on, try me.

544
00:34:59,505 --> 00:35:01,505
So you'll let it slide
no matter what I do?

545
00:35:06,775 --> 00:35:08,475
I really shouldn't.

546
00:35:15,585 --> 00:35:17,725
(Nikolay)

547
00:35:20,185 --> 00:35:21,295
(Nikolay Karamzin)

548
00:35:22,295 --> 00:35:24,795
(A Russian writer, poet,
historian, and critic)

549
00:35:28,165 --> 00:35:29,165
Anyway...

550
00:35:31,005 --> 00:35:32,705
Don't change your mind about this.

551
00:35:33,605 --> 00:35:36,805
I didn't think Momo was like that,
but I guess her true colors are showing.

552
00:35:37,775 --> 00:35:39,305
Worry about yourself.

553
00:35:42,075 --> 00:35:45,945
You always understood me and had my back,
even when I dropped out.

554
00:35:46,915 --> 00:35:48,455
If it were anyone else,

555
00:35:48,455 --> 00:35:51,555
I wouldn't care if they dated a single mom
or some middle-aged divorcée.

556
00:35:51,885 --> 00:35:53,355
What have I got to worry about?

557
00:35:54,595 --> 00:35:56,395
Honestly, I've had this thought.

558
00:35:56,925 --> 00:36:00,365
That you don't intend to get married
and just fake interest in women,

559
00:36:00,425 --> 00:36:01,935
like you're just stringing them along.

560
00:36:02,495 --> 00:36:06,035
- I sometimes think that.
- String them along? Don't be ridiculous.

561
00:36:08,605 --> 00:36:10,305
You brought it up, so spit it out.

562
00:36:12,775 --> 00:36:14,045
What worries me is that...

563
00:36:15,375 --> 00:36:18,415
maybe you lack confidence as a man.

564
00:36:24,225 --> 00:36:25,325
You mean...

565
00:36:26,025 --> 00:36:27,695
that there's something wrong with me
down there?

566
00:36:28,355 --> 00:36:30,125
No, I mean mentally.

567
00:36:31,695 --> 00:36:32,825
Unbelievable.

568
00:36:33,495 --> 00:36:35,665
Ha Yong Joong,
you're the one with the problem.

569
00:36:35,935 --> 00:36:37,965
People are a product of their environment.

570
00:36:38,035 --> 00:36:39,605
And I mostly work with women.

571
00:36:39,665 --> 00:36:42,605
My employees, actresses, reporters,
all those society wives.

572
00:36:42,675 --> 00:36:45,305
I'm telling you, it just looks like
your interest in women is superficial.

573
00:36:45,375 --> 00:36:48,615
- I've been consumed by work. You know.
- And you think I haven't?

574
00:36:48,915 --> 00:36:51,745
Babies are born even in wartime.
All it takes is the will.

575
00:36:52,285 --> 00:36:54,115
You've never brought anyone home.

576
00:36:54,255 --> 00:36:55,415
Never even introduced me to anyone.

577
00:36:55,485 --> 00:36:57,185
I need to feel that forever spark.

578
00:36:57,185 --> 00:36:59,355
What can I do if I haven't found her yet?

579
00:37:01,255 --> 00:37:02,555
The last thing that worries me is...

580
00:37:03,955 --> 00:37:05,125
that instead of women,

581
00:37:05,665 --> 00:37:06,825
you like men.

582
00:37:06,895 --> 00:37:07,995
Why you...

583
00:37:10,365 --> 00:37:12,365
I'd have an easier time understanding
if you just said you liked Ba Ra.

584
00:37:12,435 --> 00:37:15,235
Ba Ra is like a daughter to me,
if I'm being a little dramatic.

585
00:37:16,005 --> 00:37:18,645
For Mom and Dad's sake,
stay on the straight and narrow.

586
00:37:19,845 --> 00:37:22,515
- Mom might have understood.
- Ha Yong Joong.

587
00:37:22,575 --> 00:37:24,715
I was just throwing it out there.
Don't worry.

588
00:37:26,415 --> 00:37:31,285
For all our loyal listeners tuning in,
you're in for a big surprise.

589
00:37:31,355 --> 00:37:34,655
That's right,
today's special guest is Momo!

590
00:37:35,955 --> 00:37:38,265
Could you please say hello
to our dear listeners?

591
00:37:38,465 --> 00:37:39,825
Hello. This is Jin...

592
00:37:39,895 --> 00:37:40,925
(This is Jin Ju.)

593
00:37:42,735 --> 00:37:45,835
I've been wanting to come on for a while.
I'm glad you finally invited me.

594
00:37:46,235 --> 00:37:50,605
- It's Momo.
- Wait, weren't you already invited?

595
00:37:51,475 --> 00:37:53,205
Was I misinformed?

596
00:37:53,705 --> 00:37:55,115
The message never got to me...

597
00:37:56,175 --> 00:37:58,585
Well, either way,
it's an honor to have you here.

598
00:37:59,085 --> 00:38:00,085
Thank you.

599
00:38:02,885 --> 00:38:06,225
As a game developer, have you
ever thought about that kind of problem?

600
00:38:06,725 --> 00:38:09,195
Of course. I used to be addicted myself.

601
00:38:09,195 --> 00:38:10,995
How old were you when you first played?

602
00:38:11,295 --> 00:38:13,525
In elementary school,
my parents were strict,

603
00:38:13,725 --> 00:38:16,235
so I only played for short, set times.

604
00:38:16,365 --> 00:38:17,535
Was it like a whole new world?

605
00:38:17,535 --> 00:38:20,865
Yes. I got really hooked in high school.

606
00:38:21,375 --> 00:38:23,735
And that's ultimately why
I ended up dropping out.

607
00:38:23,805 --> 00:38:26,405
That's a topic our listeners
are very curious about.

608
00:38:26,405 --> 00:38:29,575
They're flooding our text line right now.

609
00:38:29,575 --> 00:38:30,715
(Ryu Ju Hyun's Connect Today.)

610
00:38:30,715 --> 00:38:32,085
(Is this a game or a form of gambling?)

611
00:38:32,845 --> 00:38:34,315
They're almost all complaints.

612
00:38:35,315 --> 00:38:39,425
When can we expect to see you
in a drama or movie again, Momo?

613
00:38:43,195 --> 00:38:44,965
It might be a while...

614
00:38:45,825 --> 00:38:49,095
With my mom gone,
I've lost a lot of my confidence.

615
00:38:50,565 --> 00:38:53,005
As a fan, I'm sad to hear that,
but I completely understand.

616
00:38:53,405 --> 00:38:56,435
A hobby might help at a time like this.

617
00:38:56,435 --> 00:38:57,605
What about scuba diving?

618
00:38:57,675 --> 00:38:58,705
I gave it up.

619
00:39:00,245 --> 00:39:02,715
I really have to ask this next question.

620
00:39:02,815 --> 00:39:06,785
Many people are sad about what happened
with you and Director Shin Ju Shin...

621
00:39:06,845 --> 00:39:09,385
and are hoping you two
might get back together.

622
00:39:10,985 --> 00:39:12,925
He deserves someone better than me.

623
00:39:14,425 --> 00:39:16,455
Do you believe in things like fate?

624
00:39:24,865 --> 00:39:25,865
How was I?

625
00:39:26,165 --> 00:39:27,235
Later...

626
00:39:28,435 --> 00:39:30,175
CEO Ha is on that other show.

627
00:39:30,235 --> 00:39:33,205
- Really? CEO Ha?
- Yes, there he is.

628
00:39:40,285 --> 00:39:42,455
- What show were you on?
- Hello.

629
00:39:45,955 --> 00:39:47,425
"Ryu Ju Hyun's Connect Today."

630
00:39:48,195 --> 00:39:50,955
We're heading out for dinner.
Do you have any plans?

631
00:39:51,525 --> 00:39:52,525
No.

632
00:39:53,125 --> 00:39:54,865
Great. Then you can join us.

633
00:39:56,295 --> 00:39:57,395
Is anyone else joining you?

634
00:39:57,935 --> 00:40:00,705
No. Tell the restaurant
one more person is coming.

635
00:40:04,175 --> 00:40:05,905
You do radio shows too?

636
00:40:05,905 --> 00:40:07,405
It was a request related to my game,

637
00:40:08,045 --> 00:40:10,875
and I wanted to explain a few things.

638
00:40:11,015 --> 00:40:12,045
Yes.

639
00:40:12,345 --> 00:40:13,545
Yes, thank you.

640
00:40:20,625 --> 00:40:21,655
Shall we go?

641
00:40:30,495 --> 00:40:32,935
- Where's Pickles?
- He's at James' place.

642
00:40:33,305 --> 00:40:35,275
- Did my brother call you?
- Yes.

643
00:40:35,875 --> 00:40:37,805
I'm sorry for bothering you.

644
00:40:37,805 --> 00:40:38,975
Not at all.

645
00:40:39,205 --> 00:40:41,315
Does Yong Joong know you're here?

646
00:40:41,775 --> 00:40:44,885
I didn't tell him. He's always so busy...

647
00:40:47,685 --> 00:40:50,715
Was there something
you wanted to talk about?

648
00:40:55,025 --> 00:40:58,565
- We're hitting rush hour traffic.
- It'll be an hour at most.

649
00:41:01,295 --> 00:41:02,395
Okay, see you in a bit then.

650
00:41:02,665 --> 00:41:03,695
Okay.

651
00:41:03,965 --> 00:41:05,705
Why don't you just ride with us?

652
00:41:06,435 --> 00:41:07,765
I drove my own car here.

653
00:41:08,375 --> 00:41:09,805
You don't have any other stops to make,
do you?

654
00:41:10,275 --> 00:41:11,275
No, I don't.

655
00:41:27,325 --> 00:41:30,755
- Find the show CEO Ha was on.
- It might not be airing yet.

656
00:41:30,825 --> 00:41:31,965
I did okay, right?

657
00:41:32,325 --> 00:41:33,325
Yes.

658
00:41:35,065 --> 00:41:36,065
What's wrong?

659
00:41:38,205 --> 00:41:41,635
Earlier, when the DJ said
it was an honor to have you,

660
00:41:41,835 --> 00:41:44,105
you should have said,
"No, the honor is all mine."

661
00:41:44,745 --> 00:41:47,945
He's much older than you
and has been in broadcasting for decades.

662
00:41:48,315 --> 00:41:50,015
He's a pretty big deal himself.

663
00:41:59,955 --> 00:42:03,855
By any chance, have you ever heard
Yong Joong talk about Momo?

664
00:42:05,195 --> 00:42:07,795
- Yes. I have.
- So you know about Yong Joong?

665
00:42:09,095 --> 00:42:10,135
Yes.

666
00:42:12,005 --> 00:42:13,935
I'm so worried something might happen
between them.

667
00:42:14,005 --> 00:42:15,505
Why did she have to cancel the engagement?

668
00:42:16,975 --> 00:42:18,405
What's your take on it?

669
00:42:18,605 --> 00:42:19,675
Do you think they're a good match?

670
00:42:21,075 --> 00:42:22,215
In terms of looks, yes.

671
00:42:22,515 --> 00:42:23,745
No, I mean their circumstances.

672
00:42:24,515 --> 00:42:26,845
She was his friend's fiancée,
which everyone knows.

673
00:42:30,885 --> 00:42:33,425
"Keep chipping away,
and it's sure to fall."

674
00:42:34,385 --> 00:42:37,855
What if Yong Joong makes a move
and she gives in?

675
00:42:39,895 --> 00:42:42,135
Can't you do something to keep them apart?

676
00:42:45,505 --> 00:42:46,935
It makes me really nervous.

677
00:42:48,205 --> 00:42:50,305
I already had a firm talk with my brother,

678
00:42:51,405 --> 00:42:53,375
but you never know
when it comes to men and women.

679
00:42:55,245 --> 00:42:57,115
You're a really great public speaker.

680
00:42:57,615 --> 00:42:58,615
So you listened to the broadcast?

681
00:42:58,885 --> 00:43:00,845
- On our way here.
- We'll have the tasting course.

682
00:43:00,915 --> 00:43:01,915
Yes, sir.

683
00:43:05,655 --> 00:43:07,325
I couldn't stop asking myself today...

684
00:43:08,425 --> 00:43:12,025
if the game I made was ruining these kids

685
00:43:12,625 --> 00:43:13,795
What are you talking about?

686
00:43:14,495 --> 00:43:16,695
I was flooded
with angry messages from parents.

687
00:43:17,295 --> 00:43:18,935
They said their kids
were losing interest in their studies.

688
00:43:19,735 --> 00:43:21,575
You can't let every single one of those
get to you.

689
00:43:22,735 --> 00:43:24,405
But I'm supposed to be
a positive force in the world.

690
00:43:25,405 --> 00:43:26,945
That's what my parents taught me.

691
00:43:28,045 --> 00:43:30,345
They were truly wonderful people,
both of them.

692
00:43:31,315 --> 00:43:35,515
If my kid were ignoring their studies
for some all-consuming game,

693
00:43:36,685 --> 00:43:38,085
I'd be really upset.

694
00:43:38,085 --> 00:43:39,825
But how is game addiction your fault?

695
00:43:40,625 --> 00:43:41,655
I made the game.

696
00:43:41,955 --> 00:43:44,765
Games themselves are fun
and a good way to relieve stress.

697
00:43:45,165 --> 00:43:46,295
It's the addiction that's the problem.

698
00:43:46,625 --> 00:43:49,565
Even without your game,
how many other addictive things are there?

699
00:43:50,335 --> 00:43:53,505
And if you stopped making them,
would games just disappear?

700
00:43:56,105 --> 00:43:59,875
People get addicted to food,
not to mention alcohol and coffee.

701
00:44:00,505 --> 00:44:04,075
Do you see anyone blaming the farmers
or the coffee producers?

702
00:44:04,745 --> 00:44:06,885
We need to eat to live.

703
00:44:07,015 --> 00:44:08,455
The problem is eating too much.

704
00:44:08,915 --> 00:44:11,015
Carb addiction, alcoholism.

705
00:44:11,455 --> 00:44:14,855
It's up to everyone to use self-control.
You have nothing to feel guilty about.

706
00:44:15,825 --> 00:44:16,825
She's right.

707
00:44:20,325 --> 00:44:22,095
Like you said on the air today,

708
00:44:22,435 --> 00:44:25,265
the game you developed
is way less violent.

709
00:44:28,135 --> 00:44:31,075
Plus, it has a great story
with a clear theme of good defeating evil.

710
00:44:31,405 --> 00:44:33,645
When you're done playing,
it makes you want to be a better person.

711
00:44:35,315 --> 00:44:36,615
That's what I was going for.
You really felt that?

712
00:44:37,075 --> 00:44:38,085
Definitely.

713
00:44:40,115 --> 00:44:41,715
That makes me feel a little better.

714
00:44:43,085 --> 00:44:44,455
You don't have any addictions, do you?

715
00:44:47,625 --> 00:44:49,655
I'm addicted to people.

716
00:44:52,325 --> 00:44:53,525
Good people.

717
00:44:56,265 --> 00:44:57,465
I hope I'm one of them.

718
00:44:58,665 --> 00:45:00,105
You get plenty of love as it is.

719
00:45:18,385 --> 00:45:19,385
Reporter Geum.

720
00:45:30,465 --> 00:45:33,465
To celebrate a successful show,
let's all have a drink tonight.

721
00:45:42,245 --> 00:45:43,875
(Momo)

722
00:45:43,945 --> 00:45:46,345
When were done drinking,
make sure Ba Ra gets home safe.

723
00:45:47,345 --> 00:45:48,355
Got it.

724
00:45:50,355 --> 00:45:51,455
You know, a man...

725
00:45:51,825 --> 00:45:53,425
can have an easy life...

726
00:45:53,555 --> 00:45:57,095
if he just listens to his mother,
his wife, and the woman on the GPS.

727
00:45:58,395 --> 00:45:59,725
My mom passed away,

728
00:46:00,525 --> 00:46:03,765
so I guess I just have to listen to my GPS
and Ba Ra.

729
00:46:09,735 --> 00:46:10,735
Let's drink while it's cold.

730
00:46:21,215 --> 00:46:24,515
Don't you want to hear me sing tonight?

731
00:46:29,025 --> 00:46:30,025
I'd love to.

732
00:46:42,205 --> 00:46:43,205
Pace yourself.

733
00:46:47,505 --> 00:46:48,815
I just want to get drunk fast.

734
00:46:49,145 --> 00:46:50,145
Why?

735
00:46:55,355 --> 00:46:57,655
Perfect. Get drunk and duck out early.

736
00:47:00,155 --> 00:47:02,025
I might as well too,
since I have both of you here tonight.

737
00:47:07,725 --> 00:47:08,735
Ba Ra.

738
00:47:19,805 --> 00:47:21,175
Have you ever been to karaoke with him?

739
00:47:21,875 --> 00:47:24,045
I've actually never heard her sing.

740
00:47:24,915 --> 00:47:26,085
You're better off not.

741
00:47:27,145 --> 00:47:28,145
It's just noise pollution.

742
00:47:32,025 --> 00:47:34,585
Is the chef still from Australia?

743
00:47:34,585 --> 00:47:35,655
Yes.

744
00:47:51,745 --> 00:47:52,745
What's wrong?

745
00:47:58,785 --> 00:48:00,845
- Tell Momo to come out here.
- Okay.

746
00:48:04,385 --> 00:48:05,385
Momo...

747
00:48:07,485 --> 00:48:09,295
Eat your steak while it's hot.

748
00:48:13,695 --> 00:48:14,935
Here you go.

749
00:48:15,335 --> 00:48:17,165
- Is it organic?
- Of course.

750
00:48:17,495 --> 00:48:19,935
I only feed my daughter organic steak.

751
00:48:23,505 --> 00:48:24,835
This reminds me of my mom...

752
00:48:25,805 --> 00:48:27,845
She always used to cut my steak for me.

753
00:48:28,645 --> 00:48:29,915
She said my hands were too weak.

754
00:48:33,185 --> 00:48:35,185
- Let me.
- No, it's okay.

755
00:49:13,425 --> 00:49:14,625
Thank you.

756
00:49:21,125 --> 00:49:22,135
Want me to cut yours?

757
00:49:24,195 --> 00:49:25,205
I'm good.

758
00:49:27,065 --> 00:49:28,935
You must be too happy to even eat.

759
00:49:30,375 --> 00:49:32,005
Not a care in the world...

760
00:49:33,205 --> 00:49:35,145
with a guy like CEO Ha watching your back.

761
00:49:39,985 --> 00:49:41,185
He's not my actual brother, though.

762
00:49:42,015 --> 00:49:44,315
Plenty of real brothers
are worse than strangers.

763
00:49:44,785 --> 00:49:45,985
Take Manager Mimi from my salon,
for instance.

764
00:49:46,525 --> 00:49:48,795
She said her older brother beat her
until she finished elementary school.

765
00:49:50,025 --> 00:49:51,095
How could he hit his own sister?

766
00:49:51,455 --> 00:49:52,465
I know, right?

767
00:49:52,925 --> 00:49:54,265
Something's wrong with him.

768
00:49:56,635 --> 00:49:57,635
(New text message)

769
00:50:00,135 --> 00:50:01,465
They booked a karaoke room for us.

770
00:50:02,235 --> 00:50:04,205
I already asked a friend to set one up.

771
00:50:04,475 --> 00:50:05,605
Really?

772
00:50:08,815 --> 00:50:09,815
Feeling any better?

773
00:50:10,745 --> 00:50:13,045
Yes, a little.

774
00:50:13,445 --> 00:50:15,455
If you'd gone to the ER,
you wouldn't have been seen right away.

775
00:50:16,115 --> 00:50:17,655
They would've run all kinds
of tests on you,

776
00:50:17,915 --> 00:50:19,185
and you'd be on medication
for over ten days.

777
00:50:20,525 --> 00:50:21,825
Did you have a good dream last night?

778
00:50:22,355 --> 00:50:23,355
No.

779
00:50:25,525 --> 00:50:26,925
All right, sit up straight.

780
00:50:27,865 --> 00:50:28,865
Slowly.

781
00:50:35,505 --> 00:50:37,405
Don't shower tonight.
Just sleep as you are.

782
00:50:38,005 --> 00:50:39,005
Just take off your outerwear.

783
00:50:39,775 --> 00:50:40,805
You shouldn't be moving around.

784
00:50:43,675 --> 00:50:46,685
I thought you only specialized
in neurosurgery.

785
00:50:50,415 --> 00:50:51,585
I can even deliver a baby.

786
00:50:52,385 --> 00:50:53,455
Try to find something I can't do.

787
00:50:56,355 --> 00:50:57,455
Get some rest,

788
00:50:57,855 --> 00:50:59,695
and be careful. It's known to relapse.

789
00:51:01,965 --> 00:51:03,065
Director Shin.

790
00:51:06,705 --> 00:51:07,705
Yes?

791
00:51:08,235 --> 00:51:09,435
Thank you.

792
00:51:10,575 --> 00:51:11,575
I mean it.

793
00:51:17,675 --> 00:51:20,345
In the quiet of the evening

794
00:51:21,545 --> 00:51:24,385
When the city lights grow dim

795
00:51:24,455 --> 00:51:27,725
I feel the rhythm in your heartbeat

796
00:51:28,425 --> 00:51:31,395
Pulling me close again

797
00:51:31,695 --> 00:51:34,025
And every step we're taking

798
00:51:34,025 --> 00:51:39,335
Feels like time is slowing down

799
00:51:41,705 --> 00:51:44,475
So hold me in this moment

800
00:51:44,605 --> 00:51:47,575
Where the world just fades away

801
00:51:47,645 --> 00:51:50,745
Let the blues keep playing

802
00:51:50,875 --> 00:51:53,845
Got a feeling we're dancing

803
00:51:53,985 --> 00:51:57,315
With you I feel the old-time magic

804
00:51:57,555 --> 00:52:00,655
Like a record softly spinning

805
00:52:00,985 --> 00:52:04,455
And I'm falling

806
00:52:04,695 --> 00:52:10,635
Falling all over again

807
00:52:23,775 --> 00:52:24,775
Yong Joong.

808
00:52:54,945 --> 00:52:57,915
Sometimes he says too much

809
00:52:59,245 --> 00:53:02,085
Sometimes nothing at all

810
00:53:04,385 --> 00:53:06,555
But I've seen his heart

811
00:53:07,225 --> 00:53:08,225
What do you want to sing?

812
00:53:09,225 --> 00:53:12,195
- I'm a horrible singer.
- That's okay. I'm a great listener.

813
00:53:12,425 --> 00:53:14,095
I'm better as a backup dancer.

814
00:53:14,425 --> 00:53:17,495
- Dancing?
- I won't walk away

815
00:53:17,565 --> 00:53:20,165
- Through the long night
- You should be the one singing.

816
00:53:20,635 --> 00:53:24,735
I'll hold your hand when it ain't right

817
00:53:25,405 --> 00:53:26,605
It's love

818
00:53:30,215 --> 00:53:33,915
- What gives? How rude.
- It must be an important call.

819
00:53:48,995 --> 00:53:50,535
What's wrong? Are you dizzy?

820
00:53:52,305 --> 00:53:55,635
(Shin Ju Shin, Director of Neurosurgery)

821
00:54:02,745 --> 00:54:04,245
(Geum Ba Ra)

822
00:54:06,585 --> 00:54:07,915
- Yes.
- Director Shin,

823
00:54:07,915 --> 00:54:10,285
we're at Silro Hotel karaoke.
Can you come here?

824
00:54:10,815 --> 00:54:12,255
- I'm on my way.
- Okay.

825
00:54:12,385 --> 00:54:16,155
(Nua General Hospital)

826
00:54:18,295 --> 00:54:19,625
Mr. Chairman. Good evening.

827
00:54:23,835 --> 00:54:25,335
How long ago did he collapse?

828
00:54:30,675 --> 00:54:33,275
It's vertigo. Director Shin's coming.

829
00:54:33,275 --> 00:54:34,305
Ju Shin is?

830
00:54:34,445 --> 00:54:35,615
We should call 911.

831
00:54:35,615 --> 00:54:37,175
No, Director Shin
can treat her right away.

832
00:54:37,475 --> 00:54:38,575
I feel nauseous.

833
00:54:39,285 --> 00:54:40,545
I think I'm going to throw up.

834
00:54:48,955 --> 00:54:50,125
It could be a vascular issue.

835
00:54:51,525 --> 00:54:52,525
Are you dizzy?

836
00:54:52,965 --> 00:54:54,365
I can't even keep my eyes open.

837
00:54:55,125 --> 00:54:57,665
The same thing happened to me,
but Director Shin fixed it right away.

838
00:54:59,105 --> 00:55:01,035
- When?
- Not too long ago.

839
00:55:01,465 --> 00:55:02,505
Why didn't you tell me?

840
00:55:04,405 --> 00:55:05,405
Why?

841
00:55:05,845 --> 00:55:07,405
Because I got better right away.

842
00:55:13,915 --> 00:55:16,385
Even though I'm dizzy, this feeling...

843
00:55:23,495 --> 00:55:24,655
Are you sure he's coming?

844
00:55:27,925 --> 00:55:29,535
The person you are calling
is on another line...

845
00:55:30,065 --> 00:55:31,065
He's on the phone?

846
00:55:40,305 --> 00:55:42,415
Was there any slurred speech
or signs of paralysis?

847
00:55:44,645 --> 00:55:45,645
Okay.

848
00:55:51,015 --> 00:55:52,085
Yes, this is he.

849
00:55:52,255 --> 00:55:55,125
A stroke patient, Mr. Lee Han Jeong, 76,
will be arriving,

850
00:55:55,355 --> 00:55:56,795
so get him straight to an emergency MRI.

851
00:56:02,665 --> 00:56:05,095
Don't worry, Mr. Chairman.
The emergency team is on standby.

852
00:56:05,765 --> 00:56:06,865
I'll be there shortly too.

853
00:56:08,135 --> 00:56:09,135
Yes, sir.

854
00:56:11,275 --> 00:56:13,675
- Is the karaoke bar in the basement?
- Yes, it's in the basement.

855
00:56:17,475 --> 00:56:18,645
Director Shin!

856
00:56:20,985 --> 00:56:22,255
Yes, Reporter Hwang, hello.

857
00:56:22,755 --> 00:56:24,085
Yes, I enjoyed your latest article.

858
00:56:37,095 --> 00:56:38,265
I think it's vertigo.

859
00:56:44,935 --> 00:56:45,945
Hurry.

860
00:56:47,605 --> 00:56:49,475
- What was she doing?
- Singing.

861
00:56:59,185 --> 00:57:00,225
Call 911.

862
00:57:01,855 --> 00:57:03,195
Our ENT Department is full.

863
00:57:07,165 --> 00:57:08,625
I just got a call
about a critical patient.

864
00:57:10,495 --> 00:57:11,495
Call 911.

865
00:57:18,945 --> 00:57:20,145
That bastard.

866
00:57:21,005 --> 00:57:23,245
Did he rush here thinking it was Ba Ra,
or what?

867
00:57:24,575 --> 00:57:26,115
This is the Silro Hotel karaoke bar.

868
00:57:32,225 --> 00:57:34,255
The phone is turned off.

869
00:57:34,325 --> 00:57:37,225
Please leave a message after the tone.

870
00:57:37,225 --> 00:57:39,195
(Momo)

871
00:57:47,265 --> 00:57:51,075
Only one guardian's allowed in the ER,
so you should go home.

872
00:57:53,175 --> 00:57:55,975
Don't worry. She'll be fine in no time,
just like I was.

873
00:57:57,175 --> 00:57:58,175
Who's coming with the patient?

874
00:57:59,645 --> 00:58:02,655
(Emergency Services)

875
00:58:21,265 --> 00:58:22,275
Hello?

876
00:58:22,935 --> 00:58:23,935
Are you with a patient?

877
00:58:24,405 --> 00:58:26,005
I just finished up.

878
00:58:26,245 --> 00:58:28,105
They said there was nothing
they could do for her in the ER.

879
00:58:28,375 --> 00:58:30,545
They said we have to wait
for the doctor tomorrow morning.

880
00:58:32,215 --> 00:58:34,945
- They didn't do an MRI, did they?
- I heard you could fix it right away.

881
00:58:35,215 --> 00:58:36,755
Ba Ra said you helped her
with her vertigo.

882
00:58:37,215 --> 00:58:38,215
Yes.

883
00:58:39,055 --> 00:58:40,055
So?

884
00:58:40,485 --> 00:58:42,125
The circumstances were different then.

885
00:58:42,625 --> 00:58:44,825
- You rushed all the way over just to...
- I told you I had a critical patient.

886
00:58:46,325 --> 00:58:47,925
Is that how little you care now?

887
00:58:47,995 --> 00:58:49,495
She'll feel better with some medicine.

888
00:58:50,895 --> 00:58:52,065
Is Ba Ra at the hospital?

889
00:58:52,735 --> 00:58:54,735
- Yes.
- Where?

890
00:58:55,265 --> 00:58:56,275
Unjin Hospital?

891
00:58:56,735 --> 00:58:59,475
Yes. Can't you call the ER for us?

892
00:58:59,545 --> 00:59:01,745
- To the doctor on duty?
- I'd get chewed out.

893
00:59:03,075 --> 00:59:04,875
Besides, there's nothing
the on-duty doctor can do.

894
00:59:05,345 --> 00:59:07,145
A doctor from the ENT Department
will be there first thing in the morning.

895
00:59:07,985 --> 00:59:09,615
She'll be fine as long as she lies still.

896
00:59:10,085 --> 00:59:11,415
You sound so detached.

897
00:59:12,425 --> 00:59:14,785
She was your fiancée, Momo.

898
00:59:14,785 --> 00:59:15,995
She was even carrying my child too.

899
00:59:18,395 --> 00:59:20,095
Emotionally, we're completely over.

900
00:59:20,765 --> 00:59:21,765
For both of us.

901
00:59:22,595 --> 00:59:23,635
Just like that?

902
00:59:24,395 --> 00:59:25,665
I'll try calling Geum Ba Ra.

903
00:59:34,475 --> 00:59:35,545
What took you so long to answer?

904
00:59:36,145 --> 00:59:37,515
I had to step out to take the call.

905
00:59:37,715 --> 00:59:39,785
I sent someone over,
so you can switch with them and go home.

906
00:59:41,285 --> 00:59:43,315
There's nothing more
you can do by staying.

907
00:59:43,915 --> 00:59:46,185
No, I need to be here.

908
00:59:46,925 --> 00:59:47,925
She's only Momo in body.

909
00:59:50,195 --> 00:59:52,155
If I were ever rushed to the ER,

910
00:59:53,525 --> 00:59:54,595
would you be by my side?

911
00:59:56,235 --> 00:59:57,235
Yes.

912
00:59:57,995 --> 00:59:59,005
And why is that?

913
01:00:00,535 --> 01:00:02,135
Like I'd ever get the chance?

914
01:00:02,475 --> 01:00:05,205
The hospital staff would be
hovering over you.

915
01:00:05,875 --> 01:00:07,975
So it was just lip service?

916
01:00:11,815 --> 01:00:12,815
Yes.

917
01:00:14,915 --> 01:00:16,985
Didn't I tell you being brutally honest
is rude and not a good look?

918
01:00:17,285 --> 01:00:18,715
You thought I was serious?

919
01:00:20,025 --> 01:00:23,055
Of course, I have to repay you
after everything you've done for me.

920
01:00:23,695 --> 01:00:25,025
I haven't personally
done anything for you.

921
01:00:26,095 --> 01:00:28,465
But thanks to you,
my vertigo was treated right away.

922
01:00:29,895 --> 01:00:30,995
So it's just to repay a debt?

923
01:00:35,105 --> 01:00:36,635
Does the reason matter?

924
01:00:36,805 --> 01:00:37,805
The intention is what matters.

925
01:00:38,835 --> 01:00:39,845
More than the reason.

926
01:00:42,045 --> 01:00:44,545
I'm always grateful. I really am.

927
01:00:45,075 --> 01:00:46,345
Then get rid of that feeling,
starting now.

928
01:00:47,645 --> 01:00:49,015
I'm not lacking for anything,

929
01:00:50,155 --> 01:00:51,415
and I'm tired of being thanked.

930
01:00:52,115 --> 01:00:54,085
I don't care for effort
born from obligation.

931
01:00:54,825 --> 01:00:57,195
- I'm not forcing myself.
- Regardless.

932
01:01:01,025 --> 01:01:02,565
Want me to look for a purebred Retriever?

933
01:01:05,595 --> 01:01:06,605
No.

934
01:01:09,835 --> 01:01:10,975
What about the critical patient?

935
01:01:11,305 --> 01:01:12,545
We got to them within the golden hour,

936
01:01:13,805 --> 01:01:14,805
so they should be fine.

937
01:01:16,345 --> 01:01:18,115
You must be exhausted.

938
01:01:18,675 --> 01:01:20,415
I don't know if I'm just breaking down
now that I'm over 30.

939
01:01:22,315 --> 01:01:23,885
But to be honest,
I was feeling a bit tired.

940
01:01:25,255 --> 01:01:26,255
But it's gone now.

941
01:01:27,155 --> 01:01:28,885
Did you see the moon that night?

942
01:01:29,795 --> 01:01:30,795
Pardon?

943
01:01:31,195 --> 01:01:32,195
Did you see it?

944
01:01:32,465 --> 01:01:33,695
Yes, I saw it.

945
01:01:34,825 --> 01:01:37,695
What do you say we talk on the phone
like this once a day?

946
01:01:39,305 --> 01:01:41,235
Would you even have the time?

947
01:01:42,035 --> 01:01:43,375
Don't phrase your refusal as a question.

948
01:01:44,075 --> 01:01:46,705
If your hands shake when you get older
and can't operate,

949
01:01:46,705 --> 01:01:48,845
switch to psychiatry.

950
01:01:50,175 --> 01:01:51,915
Ever seen a psychiatrist?

951
01:01:52,445 --> 01:01:53,445
No.

952
01:01:54,545 --> 01:01:55,545
Then see me.

953
01:01:56,055 --> 01:01:57,115
I'll be your personal doctor.

954
01:01:57,715 --> 01:01:58,715
Your all-in-one personal doctor.

955
01:01:59,525 --> 01:02:00,785
How about an MRI while we're at it?

956
01:02:02,185 --> 01:02:04,625
That's scary. Stop trying to scare me.

957
01:02:05,995 --> 01:02:07,325
Why are you afraid of so many things?

958
01:02:08,665 --> 01:02:09,865
You're scared of the rain, too.

959
01:02:10,935 --> 01:02:12,435
And yet you ran circles
around those detectives.

960
01:02:12,735 --> 01:02:15,065
That's just because I was
too naive to know any better.

961
01:02:18,005 --> 01:02:19,475
Are you a half-grown puppy now?

962
01:02:20,375 --> 01:02:21,675
Even when you get older,
don't become the tiger.

963
01:02:22,275 --> 01:02:23,715
Do people turn into tigers
when they get old?

964
01:02:24,045 --> 01:02:25,215
My mom used to say that.

965
01:02:26,085 --> 01:02:28,415
No, wait. I think I heard it from my dad.

966
01:02:30,015 --> 01:02:32,955
He said women start out as puppies
but turn into tigers as they age.

967
01:02:33,385 --> 01:02:36,725
You have times when your memory
isn't always perfect?

968
01:02:37,925 --> 01:02:40,525
Talking to you
makes me want to see your face.

969
01:02:42,195 --> 01:02:43,195
Should I come over?

970
01:02:46,805 --> 01:02:47,805
Or do you want to come here?

971
01:02:54,405 --> 01:02:57,775
Are you serious about coming over?

972
01:02:59,015 --> 01:03:00,215
You know I don't say things I don't mean.

973
01:03:01,715 --> 01:03:04,485
With your sterling character,
you can afford empty promises.

974
01:03:05,855 --> 01:03:06,855
My character?

975
01:03:07,155 --> 01:03:09,395
With your perfect resume,
family background, and character,

976
01:03:10,125 --> 01:03:12,625
adding a spoonful of empty promises
would make you absolutely perfect.

977
01:03:16,735 --> 01:03:18,965
All right. I'll work on it.

978
01:03:22,675 --> 01:03:23,675
Don't you...

979
01:03:24,475 --> 01:03:25,505
think I'm a pretty good catch?

980
01:03:26,275 --> 01:03:27,275
Be honest.

981
01:03:28,405 --> 01:03:29,475
Are you serious?

982
01:03:29,875 --> 01:03:31,545
If you don't shut me down
every now and then,

983
01:03:32,015 --> 01:03:33,015
do you get lockjaw?

984
01:03:37,085 --> 01:03:38,655
You may be a bit cold,

985
01:03:39,785 --> 01:03:41,285
but I know you're a good person.

986
01:03:42,125 --> 01:03:43,125
I can just tell.

987
01:03:45,755 --> 01:03:48,695
Okay. We'll end on that high note.

988
01:03:49,465 --> 01:03:50,465
Okay.

989
01:03:50,795 --> 01:03:52,765
Make sure you get relieved in the morning.

990
01:03:53,665 --> 01:03:54,665
I will.

991
01:04:22,895 --> 01:04:24,895
So coffee's not allowed either?

992
01:04:25,595 --> 01:04:26,935
Probably not.

993
01:04:27,705 --> 01:04:29,675
Go ask them, just to be sure.

994
01:04:34,545 --> 01:04:35,805
When did they say the test was?

995
01:04:35,875 --> 01:04:37,675
They said they'd let us know
30 minutes beforehand.

996
01:04:40,515 --> 01:04:41,515
The red phone?

997
01:04:42,785 --> 01:04:43,785
I brought it.

998
01:04:55,265 --> 01:04:57,295
If you'd gone to the ER,
you wouldn't have been seen right away.

999
01:04:57,935 --> 01:04:59,635
They would've run all kinds
of tests on you,

1000
01:04:59,635 --> 01:05:00,765
and you'd be on medication
for over ten days.

1001
01:05:03,435 --> 01:05:04,575
(Kim Gwang Cheol,
Jin Ju's Biological Father)

1002
01:05:12,215 --> 01:05:14,415
- Hello?
- This is Jin Ju's father.

1003
01:05:15,515 --> 01:05:16,515
Hello.

1004
01:05:17,255 --> 01:05:18,855
I'd like to meet with you.

1005
01:05:19,785 --> 01:05:21,955
- I'm sorry?
- I said I want to meet.

1006
01:05:25,095 --> 01:05:26,095
Okay.

1007
01:05:32,395 --> 01:05:34,335
(Nua General Hospital)

1008
01:05:50,985 --> 01:05:52,085
(The Mind)

1009
01:06:02,325 --> 01:06:04,295
(Director Shin)

1010
01:06:08,205 --> 01:06:10,035
(Director Shin)

1011
01:06:12,475 --> 01:06:15,805
- What are you up to?
- Reading and listening to some music.

1012
01:06:16,515 --> 01:06:17,775
Because you're scared of the rain?

1013
01:06:19,445 --> 01:06:20,445
Are you outside?

1014
01:06:21,215 --> 01:06:22,215
Yes.

1015
01:06:23,085 --> 01:06:25,015
It's raining. You should get home.

1016
01:06:25,515 --> 01:06:26,655
I came because it's raining.

1017
01:06:28,055 --> 01:06:29,325
You're here?

1018
01:06:29,795 --> 01:06:30,855
Yes.

1019
01:06:31,455 --> 01:06:32,595
You're at my apartment complex?

1020
01:06:33,195 --> 01:06:34,195
Yes.

1021
01:06:34,825 --> 01:06:35,965
I feel weird about coming up.

1022
01:06:36,965 --> 01:06:38,165
Come down for a minute.

1023
01:06:40,605 --> 01:06:41,605
Or should I come up?

1024
01:06:42,135 --> 01:06:43,135
I came empty-handed, though.

1025
01:06:51,215 --> 01:06:53,015
(Jaeil Apartments)

1026
01:06:53,215 --> 01:06:54,745
Going down to the first floor.

1027
01:07:23,575 --> 01:07:26,585
What brings you here?
And you even drove yourself.

1028
01:07:27,545 --> 01:07:28,715
You haven't been drinking, have you?

1029
01:07:30,415 --> 01:07:31,555
Are you asking if I came here drunk?

1030
01:07:32,615 --> 01:07:33,625
No.

1031
01:07:35,385 --> 01:07:36,725
You get scared when it rains.

1032
01:07:38,255 --> 01:07:40,325
You remembered that?

1033
01:07:43,165 --> 01:07:44,495
A little rain like this is fine.

1034
01:07:46,065 --> 01:07:47,135
My gosh!

1035
01:08:50,395 --> 01:08:53,265
(Doctor Shin)

1036
01:08:53,535 --> 01:08:56,635
- Don't get too close to Ju Shin.
- Why?

1037
01:08:56,705 --> 01:08:57,705
You saw what happened with Momo.

1038
01:08:57,705 --> 01:08:58,975
But I've decided I want to get married.

1039
01:08:59,205 --> 01:09:01,805
- Please, don't even think about it.
- Do you have any ramyeon?

1040
01:09:01,875 --> 01:09:04,045
- Are you dating Ba Ra?
- We're not quite at that stage yet.

1041
01:09:04,175 --> 01:09:05,445
Don't lead her on.

1042
01:09:07,445 --> 01:09:09,345
- Are you okay?
- This is delicious.

1043
01:09:09,345 --> 01:09:11,785
Do you really think my Jin Ju is dead?

1044
01:09:11,785 --> 01:09:13,025
Did you meet with him?

1045
01:09:13,085 --> 01:09:16,225
- What have you all done?
- Search all you want.

1046
01:09:16,625 --> 01:09:19,565
Kim Gwang Cheol can run, but I can fly.

1047
01:09:19,625 --> 01:09:21,625
Didn't he just dump Momo for Ba Ra?

1048
01:09:21,925 --> 01:09:24,565
It's no contest. I like a total old man.

1049
01:09:24,635 --> 01:09:26,335
Why Geum Ba Ra of all people?

1050
01:09:27,105 --> 01:09:29,635
You want me to pull my hair back
to prove I'm Kim Jin Ju?

1051
01:09:29,705 --> 01:09:31,605
You want me to give you
Kim Jin Ju's face back?

1052
01:09:31,775 --> 01:09:36,415
If only you could make
my fantasy a reality.

1053
01:09:36,875 --> 01:09:39,145
Why'd you propose to Ba Ra
and make her leave?

1054
01:09:39,145 --> 01:09:41,945
- Leave?
- She said goodbye to me yesterday.

1055
01:09:45,855 --> 01:09:47,855
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
